      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If it's not a severe emergency, many medical concerns can be managed at home with rest and over-the-counter meds. However, red flags that may indicate a more serious issue include severe facial weakness, numbness, weakness, or drooping on one side that worsens over time, difficulty speaking, swallowing, or blinking, sudden loss of bladder or bowel control, or severe, worsening symptoms that don't respond to treatment. If you notice any of these symptoms, seek immediate medical attention.",
